data.title: Are all lake-effect snow systems basically called snow squalls? If there are any other lake effect snow systems, what are they called?
data.meta_description: Answer (1 of 3): Snow Squalls are the winter version of a summer thunderstorm and are almost always associated with a strong arctic cold front.
